headline: Kevin O'Leary on TikTok bid: It all comes down to China's Xi
summary: Oracle (ORCL) is reportedly a top candidate to take over TikTok in the US, according to The Information. O’Leary Ventures Founder and Chairman Kevin O'Leary joins Catalysts with Madison Mills to discuss his expectations for TikTok in the US, including his own bid to buy the platform alongside Frank McCourt and Reddit (RDDT) co-founder Alexis Ohanian. Also catch Shark Tank's Kevin O'Leary weigh in on President Trump's tariff policies concerning Canada. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Catalysts here.

headline: Oracle (NYSE:ORCL) Launches AI Centre Of Excellence In Singapore For Innovation And Training
summary: Oracle (NYSE:ORCL) faced a 6.6% decline in share price over the past week amid a broader stock market downturn, which saw the market fall by 4.4%.
